        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-08T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-08T06:00:00-05:00" n="448"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Sp1/94</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-08T11:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 9, 3.20 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>818. Embassy’s 816, October 7, 10 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d448fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Spanish Government has suspended all naval authorities
                    Cadiz. President of Council states publicly that rigid investigation will be
                    held. English and Italian Ambassadors have written Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    expressing their keen disappointment and expect that immediate steps will be
                    taken to prevent escape of German submarine interned at Ferrol, in response to
                    which Government has given desired assurances. Embassy will make no
                    representations to Spanish Government pending instructions. Escape of this
                    submarine number <hi rend="italic">U–293</hi> has created profound impression
                    here. Apparently Spanish Government deeply regrets occurrence, betrays great
                    resentment towards Germany and towards Spanish officers who have been disloyal
                    to their country. French naval attaché states that Spanish officials Cadiz
                    recently gave submarine ten tons fuel oil upon request of its commander to
                    enable him to test out accumulators under repairs. Submarine was also supplied
                    with provisions but apparently no ammunition. Further information will be
                    telegraphed when it can be accurately secured.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
